  "body": "### Description\r\nIf Besu is accidentally downgraded to a lower version, the node's data can be corrupted in such as way that when the node is restarted at the correct version the node isn't usable. E.g.\r\n\r\n- Start node at `v23.10.2`\r\n- Stop node\r\n- Start node with `v23.4.3`\r\n- Node doesn't work\r\n- Stop node\r\n- Start node with `v23.10.2` again\r\n- Node doesn't work any more\r\n\r\n### Acceptance Criteria\r\nWhen starting Besu at a version lower than the highest version that has been used with that node's data, Besu should fail on startup with a clear error message, rather than attempt to start and correct the data.",
